post_text:
Bring Your Own Device Option:
Parents/Students who would like to use their own device and who do not wish to participate in the district’s 1:1 program have the option to provide their student/s with a device to bring to school to use instead of the district-owned device. Parents/Students choosing to opt-out of the 1:1 program need to fill out the BYOD form for the school year. Students' have 90 days from the beginning of school or 90 days after the student is first enrolled, whichever is later to choose BYOD to waive the $25 insurance fee. Link: https://www.fcs.org/byod

post_text:
The Findlay City Schools online remote education option, Trojan Academy, deadline has been extended through midnight on Sunday, August 16, 2020. We understand that parents needed more time to evaluate the curriculum.

If your Findlay City Schools student is already a student and you want traditional learning, you do not need to do anything. If you would like your student to receive remote education only, please sign your student up for Trojan Academy. Please note, you will not receive an email stating that you have enrolled your student; however, teachers will be reaching out with more information after the deadline. Basic school supplies can be purchased for Trojan Academy. A supply list will be given to students at a later date.

To learn more about Trojan Academy, please visit: https://fcs.org/reo/

To learn more about the reopening of schools, please visit:
https://fcs.org/faq/

School begins on September 8, 2020. #TrojanTrue

shared_text:
Family Resource Center
July 19 at 11:00 PM ·

Can you make a commitment to check in on one young person in your life this week? They are lonely too.

“Recently I had an occasion to stop and take account of my relationships and evaluate their status. What I realized is that my village has, in many ways, disappeared. There are youth in my life that I was able to invest in regularly who I no longer see due to COVID-19, or who I see much less. Without the convenience of random physical interactions, I have lost the routine investments in their life.” ~AW

FHS Community,

This morning Findlay High School was made aware of an inappropriate social media post that was allegedly made by students. This post does not represent the views or beliefs of Findlay City Schools. We take great pride in our diverse student population, as well as the education of the acceptance of all groups. We are currently in the process of investigating this incident and will address it appropriately following our board adopted policies and procedures. For more information on Findlay City Schools commitment to equity please visit our website and view our recently posted statement and video. https://fcs.org/district-about-us/

Dear Findlay City Schools Community,

This afternoon, Governor DeWine announced that all schools in the State of Ohio will remain closed for the rest of the 2019/2020 school year. With this announcement comes additional planning and considerations that we are working on. We will provide more information on the plans for the remainder of the school year tomorrow. Remote education will continue for the remainder of the year. Thank you for your support and know we are here to help and support student and families.
Mr. Edward Kurt, Superintendent #TrojanTrue

A #TrojanTrue thank you to Daniel Harmon, FHS Class of 1989
Dan is a Sergeant at the Findlay Police Department; Coordinator of Hancock County Crisis Intervention Team; Serves on numerous committees and Boards in Findlay and Hancock County; Volunteer Firefighter/Captain at Southwest Hancock County Joint Fire District
and Volunteer EMT at Appleseed EMS, Arlington.

Brian Sherman, FHS Class of 2011 is now an officer in Nashville TN. At the beginning of March Nashville, was hit by a tornado causing all officers to work two straight weeks of 12 hour shifts. Mrs. Whipkey's ESL
April 13 at 5:07 PM ·

Hello! I thought I would tell you a little bit about who we are. This year we have 50 ESL students. The countries our students represent include: Brazil,Burundi, China, Guatemala, India, Iran, Japan, Laos, Mexico, the Philippines, Puerto Rico, the United States, and Venezuela. The languages these children speak: Arabic, Chinese, English, Japanese, Kirundi, Lao, Portuguese, Spanish, Tamil, Tagalog, and Telegu.
Whittier is so fortunate to learn with these special students!
#TrojanTrue

From Mrs. Drerup's class:
I can’t say I have ever done this in my 32 years of teaching, but the birthday boy got a porch delivery today. Of course he wanted cha-cha-cha’s for his birthday song! And I even did Mrs. Hernandez’s leg kick at the end for Evan! (I hope I’m not sore tomorrow...ha,ha,ha!)
He got his birthday crown, pencil, and cup/crazy straw that everyone this year got or will get for their birthday. Hopefully this remote birthday porch visit made his day special! We have 3 other friends who have a birthday in April, too. The funny thing is they are all on the same day, April 23rd!
Thank you, Mrs. Drerup for a special delivery! FCS Teachers Rock! #TrojanTrue www.fcs.org

have been held last weekend. #TrojanTrue
shared_text:
Findlay High School Creative & Performing Arts
March 23 at 1:42 AM ·

This weekend was difficult knowing that we were missing out on performing our show. The cast, crew, & orchestra having been working so hard since January to put everything together. These kids never cease to amaze me with their talent, dedication and perseverance. Tonight I received this video that I just had to share of some of the cast practicing their songs. The emotion I felt as I watched was overwhelming! We are truly blessed to work with such an amazing group of kids.

We aren't sure how or when, but this will not be the last you see of FHS' Beauty and the Beast!

#TrojanTrue

post_text: Thanks to all of the Findlay City Schools and other volunteers who helped distribute meals today. We are blessed to have such a caring team. It was wonderful to see the smiles on each families face as we gave them their breakfast and lunch. See you Friday at Glenwood or Lincoln from 11:30-12:30. www.fcs.org #TrojanTrue
